            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/600.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/600.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork mince</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 2 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Tip: Add a little vegetable oil if the pan is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
